         <abstract>
            <p>Let $\{P_n(x)\}$ be the usual Legendre polynomials. The following integral is apparently new. $$\int^1_0P_n(2x - 1) \log \frac{1}{x} dx = \frac{(-1)^n}{n(n + 1)}\quad \text{ for } n \geqslant 1.$$ It has an application in the construction of Gauss quadrature formulas on $(0, 1)$ with weight function $\log (1/x)$.</p>
